h3. Issue Summary
Users can make mistakes and might have filled an incorrect value for the Story Points, only perceived later on, when the velocity of the team was affected. 
Fixing the story points will fix the Velocity however the Burndown Report for the affected Sprint will lose the history. 
 
h3. Steps to Reproduce
1. Create a sprint "mySprint2", assign some estimated issues (total of 8 points), and activate the sprint;
2. Create a new issue adding the story points= 229679 and assigning it to the Sprint "mySprint2", causing a scope change
3. Mark the issue as Done;
4. Complete the sprint, moving the incomplete issues to a new sprint;
5. Observe the history of the sprint:
 - The scope change when the issue with 229679 was added, 
 - The remaining estimated points for the sprint changing from 8 to 229687 points;
 - The moment when the issue was marked as done;
 - The new remaining estimated points back to 8;
 - The moment when the sprint was marked as complete, showing all done issues with estimated points 0 and the final remaining points

6. After a while, someone observed the error at the story points and how it was affecting the Team Velocity, so the value was changed from 229679 to 2;

h3. Expected Results
- Burndown reporting the story points change from 229679 to 2 and the sprint size adjusted

h3. Actual Results
- The scope change when the issue was added is not more 229679, it is showing 0.


h3. Workaround
 Currently there is no known workaround for this behavior. A workaround will be added here when available

h3. Issue Summary

 

We have seen below issue in Jira to 8.16.0

If we search for an issue in project backlog and after which we can't use the X button to clear the text,
 Apparently X button is being overridden by the "QUICK FILTER" rendered below the expanding search box
h3. Steps to Reproduce
 # go to any project backlog on Jira 8.16 and put some text in the search box 
 # try to click on the X button to clear the entered search text 

h3. Expected Results

The contents in the search box should get cleared after clicking on the X button 
h3. Actual Results

We will not be able to clear the contents in the search box by clicking on the X button 
h3. Workaround

The possible workaround is to add the below script to the announcement banner.
{code:java}
<script type="text/javascript">
jQuery(document).ready(checkSearchControl);
function checkSearchControl () {
  if($('#ghx-backlog-search').is(':visible')){
    $('#ghx-controls-plan > div').insertBefore($('#ghx-backlog-search'));
  } else {
    setTimeout(checkSearchControl, 50);
  }
}
</script>
{code}
(flag)NOTE: Please check the script in your lower environment before adding it to the prod

